cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, cite the repository metadata below. A subnet-specific Zenodo DOI will be added after the v10 release handoff is completed."
authors:
  - name: "BiobitWorks"
title: "Antigence Subnet: Decentralized Verification for AI Outputs on Bittensor"
version: 10.1.0
date-released: 2026-04-28
repository-code: "https://github.com/biobitworks/antigence-subnet"
abstract: >-
  A decentralized verification subnet for Bittensor where miners run anomaly
  detectors (antibodies), validators apply selection pressure through hidden
  evaluation datasets, and the network produces a shared trust score for AI
  outputs. Transforms Antigence's immune-inspired self/non-self detection
  paradigm into an economic incentive system. Verification-as-a-service:
  any Bittensor subnet can consume the trust signal.
license: MIT
keywords:
  - Bittensor
  - subnet
  - anomaly-detection
  - Artificial Immune System
  - Negative Selection
  - LLM Safety
  - verification-as-a-service
  - decentralized-AI
